Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve any large @broccoli florets{200} and pop onto a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{12-15%minutes}.

In the meantime, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the lemon zest, @chilli flakes{1}(add less if you'd prefer things milder), @panko breadcrumbs{25} and half the garlic. Season with @salt and @pepper and fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch it like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once cooked, transfer the toasted crumbs to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150}, @vegetable stock paste{10}, @water for the sauce{100} and season with @salt and @pepper. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20}, cooked pasta and @peas{120}. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice and stir through. Taste and add more @salt, @pepper and lemon juice if needed.

Share the creamy pasta between your #bowls{} and top with the roasted broccoli.

Finish by sprinkling over the crumb with chilli, lemon zest and garlic.

Enjoy!